        <p>
            **Keshod** is an important town and municipality in the Junagadh district of Gujarat. It is an **agricultural trade center** and features a local airport that serves the region.
        </p>

        <h2>Key Town Facts</h2>
        <div class="fact-box">
            <p><strong>Location:</strong> Junagadh District, Gujarat, India.</p>
            <p><strong>Primary Role:</strong> Agricultural and trade hub.</p>
            <p><strong>Transportation:</strong> Home to a local airport (Keshod Airport - IXK) and a railway station.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>Local Features</h2>
        <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>
                <strong>Keshod Airport (IXK)</strong><br>
                Description: Serves domestic flights, connecting the region to major cities.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Agricultural Markets</strong><br>
                Description: The town is a central marketplace for crops like groundnut and cotton grown in the surrounding area.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Local Temples</strong><br>
                Description: Features several small temples, reflecting the local religious culture.
            </li>
        </ul>
